1
00:00:05,964 --> 00:00:09,880
Guru Mahārāj, he doesn’t buy 
into the notion that

2
00:00:09,880 --> 00:00:12,545
Kṛṣṇa consciousness is
refurbished mind.

3
00:00:12,867 --> 00:00:16,310
[Kill to Live | Die to Live]

4
00:00:16,448 --> 00:00:20,739
He says, “Bhūmir āpo ’nalo vāyuḥ
khaḿ mano buddhir eva cha” 
[Bg: 7.4].

5
00:00:20,739 --> 00:00:22,965
The mundane elements.

6
00:00:22,965 --> 00:00:24,177
It’s mundane.

7
00:00:24,177 --> 00:00:26,464
The mind is mundane.

8
00:00:26,464 --> 00:00:28,253
“Woah! 
But if you think about Kṛṣṇa …”

9
00:00:28,253 --> 00:00:30,052
That’s not what 
he’s saying;

10
00:00:30,052 --> 00:00:32,046
he’s saying this needs 
to be dissolved,

11
00:00:32,046 --> 00:00:35,231
and then the spiritual mind 
can manifest.

12
00:00:35,231 --> 00:00:37,219
But this acquired mind,

13
00:00:37,219 --> 00:00:40,579
acquired intelligence, 
mind etc.

14
00:00:40,579 --> 00:00:44,184
There’re the acquired prejudices,
acquired tendencies,

15
00:00:44,319 --> 00:00:45,939
the false ego,

16
00:00:45,939 --> 00:00:49,510
that Gurudev in his famous
thought called … what was that?

17
00:00:49,510 --> 00:00:52,492
Demolishing the pillars 
of false ego.

18
00:00:52,492 --> 00:00:54,198
It has to be demolished,

19
00:00:54,198 --> 00:00:57,106
—not reconfigured or reworked
in a new way—

20
00:00:57,106 --> 00:00:59,056
demolished,

21
00:00:59,871 --> 00:01:03,135
to allow for genuine
spiritual expression.

22
00:01:04,227 --> 00:01:08,634
Got to grow something new,

23
00:01:08,634 --> 00:01:11,551
not reconfigure the old.

24
00:01:12,394 --> 00:01:16,843
Therefore the Hegelian principle,
“Die to live”,

25
00:01:16,974 --> 00:01:20,041
It doesn’t say, “No, just the way 
you are living, just, you know,

26
00:01:20,041 --> 00:01:23,518
modify that a little bit, 
and you’ll be okay.”

27
00:01:23,518 --> 00:01:26,581
That’s not “Die to live”.

28
00:01:26,581 --> 00:01:28,045
The idea in yajña,

29
00:01:28,045 --> 00:01:32,051
you throw, offer something
in the sacrificial fire,

30
00:01:32,051 --> 00:01:33,911
and it achieves
a higher position.

31
00:01:33,911 --> 00:01:35,301
What does Guru Mahārāj say,

32
00:01:35,301 --> 00:01:38,389
“What are you really suppose to offer
in the sacrificial fire?

33
00:01:38,389 --> 00:01:40,230
Your self.”

34
00:01:40,230 --> 00:01:43,588
So, the new self will come out;
that’s “Die to live”.

35
00:01:43,940 --> 00:01:46,385
He said, “As opposed to the world
that’s ruled by

36
00:01:46,385 --> 00:01:49,428
‘Kill to live’”—

37
00:01:49,428 --> 00:01:51,284
survival of the fittest.

38
00:01:51,284 --> 00:01:52,943
Jīvo jīvasya jīvanam 
[SB: 1.13.47],

39
00:01:52,943 --> 00:01:56,864
one living entity lives
by killing another one.

40
00:01:56,864 --> 00:01:58,425
That’s this world.

41
00:01:58,425 --> 00:02:02,763
Spiritual world—you live
through service, through dedication;

42
00:02:02,763 --> 00:02:05,819
by offering oneself 
in the fire of self sacrifice,

43
00:02:05,819 --> 00:02:09,519
then the new self comes out,
offer that one … in this way:

44
00:02:09,519 --> 00:02:14,464
go up, higher, nearer, 
closer to Reality.

45
00:02:14,464 --> 00:02:20,402
The reality of the beautiful self
that you possess,

46
00:02:20,402 --> 00:02:22,180
that’s also there.

47
00:02:22,180 --> 00:02:24,300
Being a part of 
Reality the Beautiful,

48
00:02:24,300 --> 00:02:29,079
you possess a beautiful self

49
00:02:29,079 --> 00:02:35,401
that is expressed through
love, devotion, dedication.

50
00:02:36,821 --> 00:02:38,729
Hare Kṛṣṇa

